reviewText: These are both great movies! I would recommend these!

I saw "My Name Is Nobody" when I was younger and I enjoyed it then as well as now. A bit different from the norm for Henry Fonda. Shot in the spaghetti western semi-comedy style of movie was very entertaining. "Cain's Cutthroats" on the other hand was a bit embarrassing to watch. I don't know it that was intentional or not, but I bought the cd for "My Name Is Nobody", and that is what the 4 star rating is for.
the funniest and good western ever! i love this movie..terence hill and henry fonda are a terrific pair in this 1973 film.if you like a goog laugh and a good western that's the one to watch!
